# Task Router
모든 사용자 요청마다 작업을 분류하고 필요한 최소 atom만 선택. 현재 요청에 필요한 것만 로드할 것.

## Step 1: Task Atom Selection (pick exactly 1)
Match user's request against keyword triggers:

|Keywords|Atom|
|---|---|
|초기화, 시작, setup, initialize, q0, bootstrap|`atoms/task/init.atom`|
|설계, 구조, 아키텍처, ADR, 어떻게 구성, 시스템 디자인|`atoms/task/plan.atom`|
|만들어, 추가, 구현, 코드, 작성, 생성, 개발, build|`atoms/task/implement.atom`|
|버그, 고쳐, 안돼, 에러, 오류, 수정, fix, 문제, 디버그|`atoms/task/debug.atom`|
|테스트, coverage, 단위, 통합, e2e, test, 검증|`atoms/task/test.atom`|
|리뷰, 검토, 확인, 컨벤션, code review, 점검|`atoms/task/review.atom`|
|문서, README, API문서, 다이어그램, document, docs, 기록|`atoms/task/document.atom`|
|배포, release, deploy, 태그, tag, publish, 출시|`atoms/task/deploy.atom`|
|마이그레이션, 업그레이드, 전환, migration, upgrade, 이전|`atoms/task/migrate.atom`|
|리팩토링, 정리, 개선(구조), refactor, cleanup, 재구성|`atoms/task/refactor.atom`|

Default: if ambiguous, use `implement.atom`.

## Step 2: Concern Atom Selection (pick 0-5)
Auto-trigger rules. Load if any condition matches:

|Condition|Atom|
|---|---|
|Task is implement, debug, or refactor|`atoms/concern/naming.atom`|
|Task is test|`atoms/concern/testing-strategy.atom`|
|Code contains async/Promise/goroutine/coroutine/await|`atoms/concern/async.atom`|
|Code performs DB write/update/delete/transaction|`atoms/concern/transaction.atom`|
|Code contains try/catch/throw/Except/Result/error handling|`atoms/concern/error.atom`|
|Code contains log/logger/console/print|`atoms/concern/logging.atom`|
|Auth/password/JWT/token/인증/인가/로그인 involved|`atoms/concern/security.atom`|
|Architecture/DB schema/API contract/environment changes proposed|`atoms/concern/approval.atom`|
|Performance/speed/optimization/느림/최적화(속도) mentioned|`atoms/concern/perf.atom`|
|Commit/PR/branch/커밋/브랜치 mentioned|`atoms/concern/git.atom`|
|Agent detects user must make a design choice (2+ valid approaches)|`atoms/concern/user-interaction.atom`|
|Exchange count exceeds 15 or user requests compression|`atoms/concern/context-lifecycle.atom`|
|File operations span multiple directories or new files needed|`atoms/concern/file-management.atom`|

## Step 3: Tech Atom Selection (pick 1-3)
프로젝트 digest(.ai.dev/DIGEST.md)와 현재 파일의 확장자/경로 기준:

|Trigger|Atom|
|---|---|
|Working with *.ts, *.tsx files|`atoms/tech/lang-typescript.atom`|
|Working with *.py files|`atoms/tech/lang-python.atom`|
|Working with *.go files|`atoms/tech/lang-go.atom`|
|Working with *.rs files|`atoms/tech/lang-rust.atom`|
|Working with *.java, *.kt files|`atoms/tech/lang-java.atom` or `atoms/tech/lang-kotlin.atom`|
|Working with *.cs files|`atoms/tech/lang-csharp.atom`|
|Working with *.php files|`atoms/tech/lang-php.atom`|
|Working with *.ex, *.exs files|`atoms/tech/lang-elixir.atom`|
|Framework code visible (imports, decorators, config)|Load matching `framework-*.atom`|
|DB migration/schema/query files|Load matching `db-*.atom`|
|Distributed/system architecture discussed|`atoms/tech/distributed-patterns.atom`|
|Large data processing discussed|`atoms/tech/data-processing.atom`|
|Async patterns discussed (alongside concern/async)|`atoms/tech/async-patterns.atom`|
|Tooling/IDE/config setup|`atoms/tech/tools.atom`|

프로젝트 digest가 없으면 작업 디렉토리의 파일 확장자로 기술 스택을 추론.

## Step 4: Augment Atom Selection (pick 0-1)
|Condition|Atom|
|---|---|
|Complex task (3+ distinct steps) or user requested examples|`atoms/augment/examples.atom`|
|User explicitly asked for thorough/careful/꼼꼼히 approach|`atoms/augment/checklist.atom`|

## Loading Rules
1. `system/identity.prompt` and `system/rules.prompt` are PERMANENT — already in context.
2. Profile atoms (`greenfield.prompt` / `migration.prompt`) are loaded once during initialization only.
3. Task atom loads first, then concern atoms, then tech atoms, then augment atoms.
4. Each atom is loaded by reading the file. Do NOT pre-load atoms speculatively.
5. After task completion, atom content should be summarized into SUMMARY.md during context compression.
6. If mid-task a new concern emerges (e.g. security issue discovered during debugging), load additional atoms immediately.
7. If task changes direction (e.g. implementing turns into debugging), load the new task atom and unload the old one during next compression cycle.
